<article class="panel legal-document">
  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how MJ Stock Magic, operated by Enjan Enterprises, handles information used by the application.</p>

  <h2>Information processed</h2>
  <p>The application processes user names, roles, permissions, inventory and supplier data, orders, receiving records, prices, kitchen schedules, audit history, technical logs, and support communications.</p>

  <h2>How information is used</h2>
  <p>Information is used to authenticate users, operate inventory and ordering workflows, prepare reports, maintain audit records, provide support, and protect the service.</p>

  <h2>Access and security</h2>
  <p>Access is restricted by assigned user roles and screen permissions. Users must not share passwords or export restricted information unless authorized.</p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>Operational and audit records may be retained for business continuity, accountability, troubleshooting, and legal or accounting requirements.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Privacy and security questions may be sent through the <a href="/support.html">Support page</a>.</p>
</article>
